<c-page style="--primary: oklch(70.36% 0.15650784384579877 257.13241640145225);">
  <page-content>
    <div class="title-header">
      <h2 class="text-title text-title-numbered">About</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose flow">
      <p class="intro">I’m Robin, a designer from the UK, and this is my blog, portfolio, and evil laboratory. It’s also the home of all my half-baked ideas and thoroughly embarrassing e-essays.</p>
      <p>Currently I’m a senior product designer at <a href="https://retool.com">Retool</a> where I help folks build punk rock software. In my spare time I also work on <a href="https://csscade.com">The Cascade</a>, a blog about CSS and front-end development.</p> 
      <p>Previously I was a staff writer at <a href="https://css-tricks.com">CSS-Tricks</a> where I wrote about the latest news in design systems, front-end development, and UI design on the web, making all sorts of <a href="https://codepen.io/robinrendle">neat demos</a> along the way.</p>
      <p>Although I grew up in the southwest of England, I now live in San Francisco where I hike around the cloudy hills of my neighborhood, brooding about websites and fonts. You can send me <a mailto="mailto:robinjrendle@gmail.com">e-mail</a> or find me on <a href="https://sfba.social/@fonts">Mastodon</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </page-content>
</c-page>

